Consulate of the United States of America at Sierra Leone

April 3rd 1875

Sir,
I have the honor to inform you that in my arrival in Sierra Leone 26 <unclear/>. I made <unclear> apphoahin</unclear> to His Excelleny Governor Kortwright for permission to act <unclear/> in my Official Capacity This permission was granted in the 2nd inst.

The Form of Consular Bond I have signed and sent to Mefs Mansfield and Roberts of Boston that they may procure the necessary securities and forward to the State Department.

The Oath of Allegiance I cannot consistently take having been born in Manchester County of Lancashire England and therefore a British subject. 

I have the honor to be
Sir,
Your obedient servant
WM Claudale

John S Cadualadee
Assistat Secretary
